==Min Nan==
===Etymology===
From [[唐山]] ''[[w:Tang Dynasty|Tang]] mountain'' + 人 ''person''
*The term [[唐山]] refers to the area that eventually came under the jurisdiction of the [[w:Tang Dynasty|Tang Dynasty]].  '''唐山人''' refers to the people who come from that area.

===Noun===
{{nan-noun|p|pojt=tng8soaN1lang5|tas=唐山人|rs=口07}}

# (''Taiwanese Min Nan'') [[w:mainlanders#Chinese mainlanders (Taiwan)|mainlander(s)]]

===Usage notes===
an old-fashioned term that was primarily used to describe non-[[w:Hoklo people|Hoklo people]] from Mainland China, a large number of whom had emmigrated to Taiwan after 1949.  This term later came to be replaced by [[gōa-séng-lâng]] ([[外省人]]).

===Synonyms===
*[[阿山]] ([[a-soaⁿ]])
*[[阿山仔]] ([[a-soaⁿ-á]])
*[[外省人]] ([[gōa-séng-lâng]])

